# Lab 2: Hosting a Web Server on the Cloud

## Objectives

* Access the AWS Console through the sandbox environment
* Launch an AWS EC2 instance
* Connect to the EC2 instance and install Nginx
* Deploy a sample web page
* Access the hosted web page through a web browser

## Background Theory

### Cloud Computing in IoT

Cloud computing provides scalable computing resources over the internet and plays a vital role in IoT applications.

### AWS EC2

Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2) allows users to create and manage virtual servers in the cloud.

### Nginx Web Server

Nginx is a lightweight and high-performance web server used for hosting websites and web applications.

## Procedure

### Step 1: Login to AWS Console

* Open AWS Academy Learner Lab.
* Start the lab.
* Launch the AWS Console.

### Step 2: Launch EC2 Instance

* Navigate to EC2 Dashboard.
* Click "Launch Instance".
* Select Ubuntu Server.
* Choose t2.micro instance type.
* Configure Security Group to allow HTTP (80) and SSH (22).
* Launch the instance.

### Step 3: Connect to EC2

```bash
ssh -i key.pem ubuntu@<public-ip>
```

### Step 4: Install Nginx

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install nginx -y
```

### Step 5: Create a Sample Webpage

Navigate to the web root directory:

```bash
cd /var/www/html
```

Edit the default page:

```bash
sudo nano index.html
```

Add:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>My AWS Website</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Hello from AWS EC2!</h1>
<p>Nginx Web Server Successfully Hosted.</p>
</body>
</html>
```

Save the file.

### Step 6: Access the Website

Open the EC2 Public IP in a browser:

```text
http://<public-ip>
```

## Output

* Successfully launched an AWS EC2 instance.
* Installed and configured Nginx.
* Hosted a sample webpage.
* Accessed the webpage through the EC2 Public IP address.

## Conclusion

The web server was successfully deployed on AWS EC2 using Nginx. The hosted webpage was accessible through a web browser using the instance's public IP address.

